WEBVTT

00:00:06.127 --> 00:00:07.670 align:center line:79%
Hey friends,
I'm Xenia, 

00:00:07.670 --> 00:00:09.338 align:center line:81%
and I'm not sure how you found yourself here.

00:00:09.672 --> 00:00:11.340 align:center line:81%
Maybe a friend invited you,

00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:13.342 align:center line:81%
maybe you heard about Alpha online.

00:00:13.342 --> 00:00:14.343 align:center line:81%
However it happened,

00:00:14.343 --> 00:00:16.304 align:center line:81%
I'm so glad that you're here.

00:00:16.304 --> 00:00:18.222 align:center line:81%
Now, if you don't know what to expect,

00:00:18.222 --> 00:00:19.515 align:center line:81%
don't worry about that.

00:00:19.515 --> 00:00:20.433 align:center line:81%
I'll be your host...

00:00:20.433 --> 00:00:22.435 align:center line:81%
well, I'll be one of your hosts.

00:00:22.435 --> 00:00:24.604 align:center line:79%
There are a few of us from 
all over the world.

00:00:25.188 --> 00:00:27.607 align:center line:79%
You ready?
- Hey!

00:00:28.066 --> 00:00:30.068 align:center line:79%
We’re off.
– Ready.

00:00:30.234 --> 00:00:32.111 align:center line:81%
Every day, from the moment we wake up,

00:00:32.111 --> 00:00:33.362 align:center line:81%
we have tons of questions

00:00:33.362 --> 00:00:35.364 align:center line:81%
to figure out and decisions to make.

00:00:35.531 --> 00:00:37.450 align:center line:79%
Isn’t that right, Micah?
- Yeah, 100 per cent.

00:00:37.450 --> 00:00:39.452 align:center line:81%
Like, what’s the playlist for today?

00:00:39.452 --> 00:00:40.745 align:center line:81%
What am I gonna wear?

00:00:40.745 --> 00:00:42.455 align:center line:81%
And, what am I gonna do with my hair?

00:00:43.623 --> 00:00:45.500 align:center line:81%
It's crazy to think, but by lunch,

00:00:45.500 --> 00:00:47.502 align:center line:81%
we've already made hundreds of decisions.

00:00:47.585 --> 00:00:48.628 align:center line:79%
Here you go, man.
- Thanks buddy.

00:00:48.628 --> 00:00:50.254 align:center line:81%
Dude, check out these snacks.

00:00:50.254 --> 00:00:51.255 align:center line:81%
What should we eat?

00:00:52.423 --> 00:00:54.967 align:center line:81%
But there are also deeper questions like:

00:00:54.967 --> 00:00:56.052 align:center line:81%
Who am I?

00:00:56.260 --> 00:00:58.262 align:center line:81%
What am I even meant to do in this life?

00:00:58.346 --> 00:01:00.723 align:center line:81%
And, what can I do to change the world?

00:01:01.682 --> 00:01:03.267 align:center line:81%
And then there are those questions,

00:01:03.267 --> 00:01:05.019 align:center line:81%
the ones that keep you up at night.

00:01:05.019 --> 00:01:07.772 align:center line:79%
Questions about relationships,
about belonging.

00:01:07.772 --> 00:01:09.315 align:center line:81%
Maybe even about faith

00:01:09.315 --> 00:01:11.442 align:center line:79%
and if God exists.
- Yeah.

00:01:11.442 --> 00:01:13.486 align:center line:81%
And, then there’s the big question:

00:01:13.653 --> 00:01:15.238 align:center line:81%
What’s the meaning of life?

00:01:15.238 --> 00:01:17.824 align:center line:79%
These are just some of the things that 
we don’t often talk about

00:01:17.824 --> 00:01:19.242 align:center line:81%
but are always in the back of our minds.

00:01:19.659 --> 00:01:21.661 align:center line:81%
And that's what Alpha is for.

00:01:21.702 --> 00:01:22.870 align:center line:81%
Yeah.

00:01:33.422 --> 00:01:36.717 align:center line:81%
<i>[Excited chatter]</i>

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:50.523 align:center line:81%
You might be thinking,

00:01:50.523 --> 00:01:52.191 align:center line:81%
“Wait, what is Alpha?”

00:01:52.191 --> 00:01:53.901 align:center line:81%
Okay, let's break it down.

00:01:53.901 --> 00:01:55.987 align:center line:79%
Over the next few weeks, 
we’re gonna get together

00:01:55.987 --> 00:01:57.697 align:center line:81%
to listen, ask questions, 

00:01:57.697 --> 00:01:59.574 align:center line:81%
and explore what truly matters.

00:01:59.740 --> 00:02:01.993 align:center line:81%
This is the space to spark conversations,

00:02:01.993 --> 00:02:02.785 align:center line:81%
process together, and 

00:02:02.785 --> 00:02:04.662 align:center line:81%
figure out what life is all about.

00:02:04.662 --> 00:02:05.371 align:center line:81%
Yeah, that's right.

00:02:05.371 --> 00:02:07.373 align:center line:79%
In each episode,
we'll hear from people

00:02:07.373 --> 00:02:09.083 align:center line:81%
of different backgrounds and ages.

00:02:09.375 --> 00:02:11.878 align:center line:81%
We will explore or unpack a different topic,

00:02:11.878 --> 00:02:14.505 align:center line:79%
and then you will have a chance 
to go a little deeper

00:02:14.505 --> 00:02:16.632 align:center line:81%
and talk about it with the people around you.

00:02:17.258 --> 00:02:19.051 align:center line:81%
A few times in each episode,

00:02:19.051 --> 00:02:20.261 align:center line:81%
we're gonna prompt some questions

00:02:20.344 --> 00:02:22.346 align:center line:81%
and hear some answers from around the world.

00:02:22.388 --> 00:02:24.515 align:center line:81%
And then it’s over to you and your group.

00:02:24.515 --> 00:02:25.266 align:center line:81%
And, if you like,

00:02:25.266 --> 00:02:26.267 align:center line:81%
you can share what you think,

00:02:26.267 --> 00:02:27.268 align:center line:81%
but no pressure.

00:02:27.393 --> 00:02:29.395 align:center line:79%
We’ll be sharing insights from a 
Christian point of view.

00:02:29.770 --> 00:02:31.063 align:center line:81%
Yeah I know, just mentioning the word

00:02:31.063 --> 00:02:32.982 align:center line:81%
‘Christian’ may get some of you thinking,

00:02:32.982 --> 00:02:35.151 align:center line:79%
“Am I gonna be the only 
one here who doesn’t believe

00:02:35.151 --> 00:02:37.153 align:center line:81%
in any of this stuff, or who has doubts?”

00:02:37.153 --> 00:02:38.070 align:center line:81%
If that's you,

00:02:38.070 --> 00:02:38.905 align:center line:81%
hey, that’s okay.

00:02:38.905 --> 00:02:40.239 align:center line:81%
Alpha is for you.

00:02:40.239 --> 00:02:41.991 align:center line:81%
There's no expectation for you to agree with 

00:02:41.991 --> 00:02:44.452 align:center line:81%
anything or everything that’s talked about.

00:02:44.493 --> 00:02:46.495 align:center line:81%
This is about exploring together.

00:02:46.704 --> 00:02:48.706 align:center line:81%
So, what's on your mind?

00:02:49.081 --> 00:02:51.417 align:center line:81%
Why do bad things happen to good people?

00:02:51.542 --> 00:02:53.377 align:center line:81%
Is God really everywhere?

00:02:53.377 --> 00:02:56.047 align:center line:81%
Will I be able to achieve all of my dreams?

00:02:56.172 --> 00:02:59.050 align:center line:79%
How is social media affecting the 
mental health of this generation?

00:02:59.675 --> 00:03:02.386 align:center line:79%
How can I study harder 
but also balance it with my home life?

00:03:02.595 --> 00:03:04.639 align:center line:81%
Why is there war?

00:03:05.681 --> 00:03:07.433 align:center line:81%
What is the plan for my life?

00:03:08.517 --> 00:03:10.269 align:center line:81%
How can I influence my surroundings?

00:03:11.187 --> 00:03:13.481 align:center line:79%
Why am I going through 
mental health problems?

00:03:13.689 --> 00:03:17.151 align:center line:81%
Is it normal to doubt myself but trust God?

00:03:17.944 --> 00:03:19.737 align:center line:81%
How do I maintain real connection

00:03:19.737 --> 00:03:20.863 align:center line:81%
in this virtual world?

00:03:28.162 --> 00:03:30.164 align:center line:81%
Of all the questions we have in our heads,

00:03:30.164 --> 00:03:31.082 align:center line:81%
here’s one:

00:03:31.082 --> 00:03:33.084 align:center line:81%
What makes you happy?

00:03:34.377 --> 00:03:35.211 align:center line:81%
Hi.

00:03:35.211 --> 00:03:37.797 align:center line:79%
I’m Jesse, and I’m going 
around the world asking people

00:03:37.797 --> 00:03:39.840 align:center line:81%
some of the life's biggest questions.

00:03:39.924 --> 00:03:41.926 align:center line:81%
What makes you happy?

00:03:41.926 --> 00:03:42.426 align:center line:81%
Ugh...

00:03:42.426 --> 00:03:43.135 align:center line:81%
Um...

00:03:43.135 --> 00:03:44.178 align:center line:81%
What makes me happy?

00:03:44.178 --> 00:03:45.388 align:center line:81%
Probably just hanging out with friends.

00:03:45.388 --> 00:03:46.138 align:center line:81%
Dancing.

00:03:46.138 --> 00:03:47.139 align:center line:81%
Acting.

00:03:47.139 --> 00:03:48.182 align:center line:81%
I like to sing.

00:03:48.182 --> 00:03:49.141 align:center line:81%
Figure skating.

00:03:49.141 --> 00:03:49.850 align:center line:81%
Drawing.

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:50.851 align:center line:81%
I love drawing.

00:03:50.851 --> 00:03:52.311 align:center line:81%
What makes you happy?

00:03:52.311 --> 00:03:53.062 align:center line:81%
Track.

00:03:53.062 --> 00:03:54.230 align:center line:81%
I think playing volleyball.

00:03:54.230 --> 00:03:55.606 align:center line:81%
Basketball.

00:03:55.606 --> 00:03:56.274 align:center line:81%
God.

00:03:56.274 --> 00:03:57.566 align:center line:81%
My family and friends.

00:03:57.566 --> 00:03:58.651 align:center line:81%
Nice cars.

00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:00.403 align:center line:81%
Shopping. Money.

00:04:00.403 --> 00:04:02.029 align:center line:81%
Dogs and cats.

00:04:02.029 --> 00:04:02.697 align:center line:81%
Uh... travelling.

00:04:02.697 --> 00:04:03.656 align:center line:81%
Creating music.

00:04:03.656 --> 00:04:06.617 align:center line:79%
Playing piano, guitar, 
all sorts of instruments.

00:04:06.617 --> 00:04:08.828 align:center line:81%
I love music, And I love my AirPods.

00:04:09.078 --> 00:04:10.204 align:center line:81%
Sleeping.

00:04:10.204 --> 00:04:10.997 align:center line:81%
Sleeping?

00:04:10.997 --> 00:04:11.747 align:center line:81%
Yes.

00:04:11.747 --> 00:04:13.749 align:center line:81%
Baby Yoda makes me happy.

00:04:13.833 --> 00:04:14.834 align:center line:81%
Parents’ love.

00:04:14.834 --> 00:04:16.127 align:center line:81%
Reading a really good book.

00:04:16.127 --> 00:04:17.253 align:center line:81%
Eating good food.

00:04:17.253 --> 00:04:18.462 align:center line:81%
What makes you happy?

00:04:18.462 --> 00:04:19.338 align:center line:81%
Pizza.

00:04:21.257 --> 00:04:23.134 align:center line:81%
Just laughter in general makes me happy.

00:04:23.134 --> 00:04:24.760 align:center line:81%
Making other people happy.

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:26.304 align:center line:81%
Probably just living my best life.

00:04:26.304 --> 00:04:27.096 align:center line:81%
Do whatever I want, you know?

00:04:27.096 --> 00:04:28.931 align:center line:81%
I'm happy when I'm with friends.

00:04:28.931 --> 00:04:30.933 align:center line:81%
Everything with friends is better.

00:04:30.933 --> 00:04:33.185 align:center line:81%
If I get a hug from anyone, I feel happy.

00:04:33.185 --> 00:04:34.729 align:center line:81%
Look at your piece, massive.

00:04:37.189 --> 00:04:42.987 align:center line:81%
[What makes you happy?]

00:04:55.624 --> 00:04:57.835 align:center line:81%
You know that amazing feeling you get,

00:04:57.835 --> 00:04:59.295 align:center line:81%
when you pull off something incredible?

00:05:00.463 --> 00:05:01.881 align:center line:81%
Well that happens to us,

00:05:01.881 --> 00:05:03.883 align:center line:81%
all the time.

00:05:03.883 --> 00:05:05.926 align:center line:81%
<i>[Cheering]</i>

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:08.637 align:center line:81%
We call ourselves

00:05:08.637 --> 00:05:09.722 align:center line:81%
How Ridiculous

00:05:09.722 --> 00:05:12.141 align:center line:79%
because we just do the craziest things 
we can think of.

00:05:12.475 --> 00:05:13.976 align:center line:81%
People seem to love it.

00:05:14.393 --> 00:05:16.395 align:center line:81%
This is ten glass windows.

00:05:18.981 --> 00:05:21.776 align:center line:81%
Giant, spiky, mace ball of death.

00:05:25.613 --> 00:05:27.073 align:center line:81%
Oh my goodness.

00:05:27.073 --> 00:05:28.157 align:center line:81%
Oh my goodness.

00:05:33.788 --> 00:05:35.915 align:center line:81%
It all started more than 14 years ago.

00:05:35.956 --> 00:05:37.917 align:center line:81%
We were just a group of childhood mates

00:05:37.917 --> 00:05:38.751 align:center line:81%
with basketballs,

00:05:38.751 --> 00:05:40.753 align:center line:81%
trying to see who could make the best shot.

00:05:41.170 --> 00:05:43.005 align:center line:81%
And from there, we just kept doing bigger

00:05:43.005 --> 00:05:44.382 align:center line:81%
and better things.

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:47.718 align:center line:79%
We first discovered 
How Ridiculous on YouTube.

00:05:49.303 --> 00:05:50.096 align:center line:81%
Get in!

00:05:50.096 --> 00:05:51.305 align:center line:81%
<i>[Cheering]</i>

00:05:52.306 --> 00:05:54.558 align:center line:79%
And soon found ourselves 
travelling the world,

00:05:54.558 --> 00:05:56.644 align:center line:81%
in the most amazing locations doing stuff

00:05:56.644 --> 00:05:58.396 align:center line:81%
we could have never dreamed of.

00:05:58.396 --> 00:06:00.106 align:center line:81%
We got a catching competition

00:06:00.106 --> 00:06:02.316 align:center line:81%
from a 165-metre dam.

00:06:02.316 --> 00:06:03.484 align:center line:81%
Go Rexy!

00:06:03.484 --> 00:06:04.944 align:center line:81%
Get to space!

00:06:06.737 --> 00:06:08.739 align:center line:81%
It’s one small step for man.

00:06:10.241 --> 00:06:13.452 align:center line:81%
Ten million subscribers!

00:06:13.452 --> 00:06:15.079 align:center line:81%
How good!

00:06:18.290 --> 00:06:20.292 align:center line:81%
That happiness didn't last long.

00:06:20.543 --> 00:06:22.503 align:center line:81%
One thing we quickly realised

00:06:22.503 --> 00:06:24.547 align:center line:81%
is that you can't do the same trick twice.

00:06:24.547 --> 00:06:26.841 align:center line:81%
You always got to find the next big thing.

00:06:26.924 --> 00:06:28.676 align:center line:81%
There's that GoPro also

00:06:28.676 --> 00:06:29.552 align:center line:81%
at the top.

00:06:29.552 --> 00:06:30.719 align:center line:81%
But the problem with that,

00:06:30.719 --> 00:06:32.721 align:center line:79%
it’s that, you know, 
when things were going badly

00:06:32.721 --> 00:06:35.599 align:center line:79%
when the views were lower than I’d hoped 
or we expected.

00:06:36.183 --> 00:06:37.268 align:center line:81%
I’d get really down.

00:06:37.268 --> 00:06:38.894 align:center line:81%
I’d feel depressed,

00:06:38.894 --> 00:06:40.771 align:center line:79%
which really– 
it’s not a fun place to be.

00:06:41.272 --> 00:06:43.274 align:center line:81%
When I'm in the valley moments,

00:06:43.274 --> 00:06:44.358 align:center line:81%
what I'm thinking is like,

00:06:44.358 --> 00:06:45.985 align:center line:81%
I... I really need to put my hope

00:06:45.985 --> 00:06:47.987 align:center line:81%
in something better than this.

00:06:48.237 --> 00:06:49.405 align:center line:81%
There's gotta be something else.

00:06:49.405 --> 00:06:50.739 align:center line:81%
There’s gotta be something more.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.085 align:center line:81%
Some people think money, fame,

00:07:03.085 --> 00:07:05.838 align:center line:79%
and relationships would 
solve a lot of their problems.

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:08.340 align:center line:79%
A lot of the times, 
we chase after these things

00:07:08.340 --> 00:07:10.551 align:center line:81%
only to discover that they aren't the answer.

00:07:10.759 --> 00:07:13.762 align:center line:79%
Reality TV star Kylie Jenner 
has shared in the past

00:07:13.888 --> 00:07:15.222 align:center line:81%
that growing up in the limelight

00:07:15.222 --> 00:07:17.224 align:center line:81%
has caused her to lose herself at times

00:07:17.516 --> 00:07:19.518 align:center line:81%
and experience terrible anxiety.

00:07:19.852 --> 00:07:21.854 align:center line:81%
In one interview she said,

00:07:21.854 --> 00:07:24.648 align:center line:79%
“I wake up every morning 
with the worst anxiety.

00:07:24.940 --> 00:07:26.358 align:center line:81%
I don’t know why.”

00:07:26.358 --> 00:07:28.486 align:center line:81%
For me, I thought it was education.

00:07:28.819 --> 00:07:30.988 align:center line:81%
Going to university was my big dream.

00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:33.991 align:center line:79%
And everyone said that 
it’s the best time of your life,

00:07:34.241 --> 00:07:35.826 align:center line:81%
and it's where you find yourself, and

00:07:35.826 --> 00:07:37.453 align:center line:81%
you can do whatever you want.

00:07:37.745 --> 00:07:39.497 align:center line:81%
But... when I got there,

00:07:39.497 --> 00:07:41.665 align:center line:81%
the reality didn't live up to the dream.

00:07:42.082 --> 00:07:45.794 align:center line:79%
I was worried about doing the wrong thing
and making mistakes.

00:07:45.794 --> 00:07:48.255 align:center line:81%
And the pressure of it all got to me,

00:07:48.255 --> 00:07:50.049 align:center line:81%
and it was overwhelming.

00:07:50.049 --> 00:07:52.343 align:center line:79%
It didn’t make me as 
happy as I thought it would.

00:07:52.885 --> 00:07:55.554 align:center line:81%
So how do we find true happiness?

00:08:06.982 --> 00:08:08.609 align:center line:81%
Everybody wants to be happy,

00:08:08.609 --> 00:08:09.693 align:center line:81%
including me.

00:08:09.735 --> 00:08:11.737 align:center line:81%
But I'd say it's not everything.

00:08:12.738 --> 00:08:13.906 align:center line:79%
I've heard it said that
it’s like we got this 

00:08:13.906 --> 00:08:15.491 align:center line:81%
happiness bucket in our heart,

00:08:15.741 --> 00:08:16.617 align:center line:81%
and we’re all constantly trying

00:08:16.617 --> 00:08:18.118 align:center line:81%
to fill it with different things.

00:08:18.118 --> 00:08:19.119 align:center line:81%
I know, for me,

00:08:19.161 --> 00:08:20.746 align:center line:81%
I tried to fill it with chasing status,

00:08:20.746 --> 00:08:21.789 align:center line:81%
 relationships,

00:08:21.830 --> 00:08:23.832 align:center line:79%
trying to get respect and 
approval off my mates.

00:08:24.208 --> 00:08:25.543 align:center line:81%
But even when I got some of those things,

00:08:25.543 --> 00:08:27.002 align:center line:81%
I was still left feeling empty.

00:08:27.002 --> 00:08:28.796 align:center line:81%
I ended up going from unhealthy relationship

00:08:28.796 --> 00:08:30.631 align:center line:81%
to unhealthy relationship.

00:08:30.631 --> 00:08:32.174 align:center line:81%
I bought things I didn’t need

00:08:32.174 --> 00:08:33.175 align:center line:81%
just to impress people,

00:08:33.175 --> 00:08:34.635 align:center line:81%
to fit in and belong.

00:08:34.802 --> 00:08:36.804 align:center line:81%
I was just left wondering like, surely...

00:08:36.971 --> 00:08:38.973 align:center line:81%
surely there must be more to life than this.

00:08:39.390 --> 00:08:41.392 align:center line:81%
And I wonder if you've ever felt the same?

00:08:41.392 --> 00:08:42.768 align:center line:81%
And no matter how hard you try,

00:08:42.768 --> 00:08:44.770 align:center line:81%
nothing seems to satisfy that longing

00:08:44.812 --> 00:08:45.896 align:center line:81%
that’s in each and every one of us 

00:08:45.896 --> 00:08:46.939 align:center line:81%
to be truly happy.

00:08:47.898 --> 00:08:49.066 align:center line:81%
Jesus, who’s the central figure

00:08:49.066 --> 00:08:50.359 align:center line:81%
of the Christian faith,

00:08:50.359 --> 00:08:52.278 align:center line:81%
spoke to this longing that we feel.

00:08:52.278 --> 00:08:53.696 align:center line:81%
He says, “I am the bread of life.

00:08:53.696 --> 00:08:55.823 align:center line:81%
Anyone who comes to me will never be hungry.

00:08:56.448 --> 00:08:58.742 align:center line:79%
Anyone who believes in me 
will never be thirsty.”

00:08:59.118 --> 00:09:00.703 align:center line:79%
Now if you’re hearing that 
for the first time,

00:09:00.703 --> 00:09:02.496 align:center line:81%
it might sound a little bit strange.

00:09:02.496 --> 00:09:04.498 align:center line:79%
But Jesus isn’t talking about 
a physical hunger

00:09:04.498 --> 00:09:06.208 align:center line:81%
that can be fixed with some food,

00:09:06.208 --> 00:09:08.085 align:center line:79%
or a thirst that can be 
fixed with some drink.

00:09:08.752 --> 00:09:10.504 align:center line:81%
He’s talking about another type of hunger,

00:09:10.504 --> 00:09:11.964 align:center line:81%
another type of thirst.

00:09:11.964 --> 00:09:13.215 align:center line:81%
He's talking about a longing

00:09:13.215 --> 00:09:15.426 align:center line:81%
for meaning, purpose, and love.

00:09:15.801 --> 00:09:17.344 align:center line:81%
And what Jesus is saying is that

00:09:17.344 --> 00:09:19.430 align:center line:81%
he is the one that satisfies that longing,

00:09:19.722 --> 00:09:21.932 align:center line:81%
that hunger that's in every human heart.

00:09:22.641 --> 00:09:24.351 align:center line:81%
Now if what Jesus is saying is true,

00:09:24.351 --> 00:09:25.269 align:center line:81%
then it matters.

00:09:25.269 --> 00:09:26.395 align:center line:81%
It matters to us all.

00:09:27.062 --> 00:09:28.105 align:center line:81%
I know it matters to me.

00:09:28.564 --> 00:09:30.441 align:center line:81%
My teenage years were messed up.

00:09:30.441 --> 00:09:32.526 align:center line:79%
But it was my encounter with Jesus 
that changed everything.

00:09:33.027 --> 00:09:34.737 align:center line:81%
Doesn't mean my life became perfect,

00:09:34.737 --> 00:09:36.739 align:center line:81%
but I found that in my imperfection

00:09:36.739 --> 00:09:37.781 align:center line:81%
and my brokenness, 

00:09:37.781 --> 00:09:38.824 align:center line:81%
I encountered a peace

00:09:39.241 --> 00:09:40.284 align:center line:81%
and a hope for my future.

00:09:41.577 --> 00:09:42.494 align:center line:81%
Maybe you’re sitting there saying,

00:09:42.494 --> 00:09:43.621 align:center line:81%
“Well just... just hold on a minute. Like,

00:09:43.621 --> 00:09:44.705 align:center line:81%
who is Jesus

00:09:44.705 --> 00:09:45.998 align:center line:81%
and why are we even talking about him?

00:09:46.582 --> 00:09:47.791 align:center line:81%
How do you know what he said is true 

00:09:47.791 --> 00:09:48.959 align:center line:81%
or even relevant?”

00:09:49.585 --> 00:09:51.503 align:center line:79%
Well that’s what we’re gonna be 
looking at together,

00:09:51.503 --> 00:09:53.505 align:center line:81%
on Alpha.

00:09:57.593 --> 00:09:59.094 align:center line:81%
I've always loved setting myself

00:09:59.094 --> 00:10:01.096 align:center line:81%
big, ambitious challenges.

00:10:01.305 --> 00:10:02.890 align:center line:81%
There’s no feeling like winning.

00:10:04.099 --> 00:10:05.768 align:center line:81%
One of our greatest ever moments was

00:10:05.768 --> 00:10:07.144 align:center line:81%
when we made a world record

00:10:07.227 --> 00:10:09.271 align:center line:81%
basketball shot from 200 metres up.

00:10:12.858 --> 00:10:14.693 align:center line:81%
Yes! Yeah!

00:10:14.693 --> 00:10:16.695 align:center line:81%
It went in! It went in!

00:10:16.904 --> 00:10:19.948 align:center line:81%
Yeah! Thank God! Yes!

00:10:21.950 --> 00:10:23.035 align:center line:81%
Honestly, that was like

00:10:23.035 --> 00:10:25.871 align:center line:81%
the biggest moment of pure joy I've ever had.

00:10:26.664 --> 00:10:29.458 align:center line:81%
It fills you with a sense of satisfaction.

00:10:29.667 --> 00:10:32.336 align:center line:79%
It fills you with a sense 
of an adrenaline hit.

00:10:32.336 --> 00:10:34.588 align:center line:79%
So you’ve worked out a Barina 
can bounce on a trampoline,

00:10:34.588 --> 00:10:36.131 align:center line:10%
the world's strongest trampoline.

00:10:36.131 --> 00:10:37.549 align:center line:10%
What's... what's next?

00:10:37.549 --> 00:10:39.551 align:center line:10%
After these records,

00:10:39.718 --> 00:10:42.179 align:center line:81%
they always ask, “So what’s next?”

00:10:42.262 --> 00:10:45.265 align:center line:81%
It just makes me realise that impressing

00:10:45.265 --> 00:10:47.601 align:center line:81%
people is a never-ending pursuit.

00:10:48.268 --> 00:10:50.354 align:center line:81%
Nothing's ever gonna be enough.

00:10:53.982 --> 00:10:56.026 align:center line:81%
I think at the absolute heart of the matter

00:10:56.026 --> 00:10:58.529 align:center line:81%
is almost like an issue of hope.

00:10:58.570 --> 00:11:00.572 align:center line:81%
Like, what am I putting my hope in?

00:11:00.781 --> 00:11:02.157 align:center line:81%
If my hope is in

00:11:02.157 --> 00:11:04.618 align:center line:81%
views, and fame, and popularity, 

00:11:04.618 --> 00:11:07.329 align:center line:79%
at some point
that's gonna let me down.

00:11:08.455 --> 00:11:10.457 align:center line:81%
And the reality for me,

00:11:10.457 --> 00:11:13.210 align:center line:81%
my hope has to be in Jesus.

00:11:13.836 --> 00:11:16.171 align:center line:81%
He fulfils what the world cannot.

00:11:17.005 --> 00:11:19.007 align:center line:81%
He loves me unconditionally.

00:11:19.299 --> 00:11:20.884 align:center line:81%
When I don't perform,

00:11:20.884 --> 00:11:22.428 align:center line:81%
when things don't go well, 

00:11:22.428 --> 00:11:24.513 align:center line:79%
I'm not abandoned,
I'm not rejected.

00:11:24.513 --> 00:11:26.515 align:center line:81%
Ultimately, it helps me

00:11:26.974 --> 00:11:29.393 align:center line:81%
have more joy, more happiness,

00:11:30.185 --> 00:11:32.187 align:center line:81%
but in a truer way.

00:11:33.063 --> 00:11:34.231 align:center line:81%
One of the things we love to do


00:11:34.231 --> 00:11:35.399 align:center line:81%
that helps keep us grounded

00:11:35.399 --> 00:11:36.859 align:center line:81%
is come together and pray.

00:11:37.192 --> 00:11:39.236 align:center line:81%
Thank you Lord for an amazing day.

00:11:39.611 --> 00:11:41.780 align:center line:81%
Wow... How Ridiculous is such a blessing.

00:11:42.948 --> 00:11:44.324 align:center line:81%
Sort of helps remind us that 

00:11:44.324 --> 00:11:45.909 align:center line:81%
what happens on the shoot is

00:11:45.909 --> 00:11:47.619 align:center line:81%
not the only thing happening on the earth.

00:11:47.619 --> 00:11:49.204 align:center line:81%
Go! Right there!

00:11:52.291 --> 00:11:54.710 align:center line:81%
So if a video doesn't perform well,

00:11:54.710 --> 00:11:56.378 align:center line:81%
we ultimately all know that

00:11:57.588 --> 00:12:00.382 align:center line:81%
this isn’t the be-all and end-all.

