Why aren't you here yet?

00:17:35.592 --> 00:17:37.552 align:center line:81%
What you been up to?

00:17:37.552 --> 00:17:38.553 align:center line:81%
What you doing?

00:17:38.553 --> 00:17:40.097 align:center line:81%
What is the point of all of this?

00:17:40.097 --> 00:17:41.848 align:center line:81%
Like we're just here, we're working.

00:17:41.848 --> 00:17:43.683 align:center line:81%
You just work, work, work ,work, work...

00:17:43.683 --> 00:17:44.976 align:center line:81%
What's next?

00:17:44.976 --> 00:17:46.853 align:center line:81%
I really don't know, honestly.

00:17:46.853 --> 00:17:47.938 align:center line:81%
Maybe how much he loves me?

00:17:47.938 --> 00:17:49.523 align:center line:81%
Not really sure.

00:17:49.523 --> 00:17:50.941 align:center line:81%
I haven't really done much.

00:17:50.941 --> 00:17:52.567 align:center line:81%
I don't feel like I could ask for anything.

00:17:54.986 --> 00:17:56.988 align:center line:81%
If God exists, what would you ask?

00:17:57.155 --> 00:17:59.241 align:center line:81%
His thought process in creating the world.

00:17:59.241 --> 00:18:00.408 align:center line:81%
Because it’s like really beautiful.

00:18:00.408 --> 00:18:02.410 align:center line:79%
Why are people hungry 
when there’s so much food?

00:18:02.536 --> 00:18:04.412 align:center line:79%
There’s so much abundance 
but so much lack.

00:18:04.412 --> 00:18:05.997 align:center line:81%
What was the purpose of creating me?

00:18:05.997 --> 00:18:07.249 align:center line:81%
Why does evil exist?

00:18:07.249 --> 00:18:09.251 align:center line:81%
Is there life after death?

00:18:09.501 --> 00:18:10.961 align:center line:81%
Is it peaceful?

00:18:10.961 --> 00:18:12.254 align:center line:81%
Would I be happy or

00:18:12.254 --> 00:18:13.880 align:center line:81%
would I just be like, ‘poof’?

00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:16.550 align:center line:79%
What happens to those of different faiths 
after we die?

00:18:16.675 --> 00:18:17.843 align:center line:81%
Does heaven exist then,

00:18:17.843 --> 00:18:18.969 align:center line:81%
and how do I get there?

00:18:18.969 --> 00:18:20.011 align:center line:81%
What is my purpose?

00:18:20.011 --> 00:18:21.847 align:center line:81%
I’d ask if I’m on the right track 

00:18:21.847 --> 00:18:23.056 align:center line:81%
and, if not,

00:18:23.056 --> 00:18:25.267 align:center line:81%
how I can continue to be on the right path?

00:18:28.937 --> 00:18:36.736 align:center line:81%
[If God exists, what would you ask?]

00:18:47.455 --> 00:18:48.290 align:center line:81%
Jesus said,

00:18:48.290 --> 00:18:50.000 align:center line:81%
“I have come so that you may have life,

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:51.418 align:center line:81%
and life to the full.”

00:18:51.501 --> 00:18:53.253 align:center line:81%
The kind of life that Jesus is describing

00:18:53.253 --> 00:18:54.796 align:center line:81%
is a life full of love,

00:18:55.130 --> 00:18:57.132 align:center line:81%
joy, peace and purpose.

00:18:57.132 --> 00:18:59.843 align:center line:79%
It’s a life free from trying to 
fill a leaking bucket,

00:18:59.843 --> 00:19:02.512 align:center line:81%
with 'enough' to finally feel fulfilled.

00:19:03.054 --> 00:19:05.724 align:center line:79%
Jesus says, 
“I am the way, the truth, and the life.”

00:19:06.224 --> 00:19:08.518 align:center line:81%
What Jesus is saying is that, “I am the way

00:19:08.518 --> 00:19:11.188 align:center line:79%
to a loving and lasting 
relationship with God.”

00:19:11.605 --> 00:19:14.357 align:center line:79%
A relationship that fills 
the emptiness within all of us.

00:19:14.941 --> 00:19:16.860 align:center line:81%
When he says, “I am the truth”,

00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:18.361 align:center line:81%
it’s more than just head-knowledge,

00:19:18.528 --> 00:19:19.988 align:center line:81%
but it's knowing the truth in your heart 

00:19:19.988 --> 00:19:22.657 align:center line:79%
that you are loved
and accepted by God.

00:19:22.657 --> 00:19:25.619 align:center line:81%
And with him, you can live life to the full.

00:19:25.619 --> 00:19:26.703 align:center line:81%
A life of meaning,

00:19:26.703 --> 00:19:27.996 align:center line:81%
a life of purpose, 

00:19:27.996 --> 00:19:29.581 align:center line:81%
and a life worth living.

00:19:29.998 --> 00:19:32.083 align:center line:79%
Over the next few weeks, 
we’re gonna explore

00:19:32.083 --> 00:19:33.543 align:center line:81%
how Jesus has made this possible 

00:19:33.543 --> 00:19:35.462 align:center line:81%
for you and for me.

00:19:35.754 --> 00:19:37.797 align:center line:79%
That doesn’t mean 
everything’s gonna be perfect;

00:19:37.923 --> 00:19:39.382 align:center line:81%
things still go wrong.

00:19:39.382 --> 00:19:41.051 align:center line:81%
But, because of Jesus, 

00:19:41.051 --> 00:19:42.719 align:center line:81%
we have a hope and a purpose,

00:19:42.719 --> 00:19:44.429 align:center line:81%
even when we face challenges.

00:19:44.429 --> 00:19:46.640 align:center line:81%
And it means we don't have to do it alone.

00:19:47.182 --> 00:19:49.601 align:center line:81%
And on Alpha, we're going to be on a journey

00:19:49.601 --> 00:19:51.603 align:center line:81%
to explore all of this together.

00:19:51.686 --> 00:19:53.480 align:center line:81%
So wherever you're coming from, feel free

00:19:53.480 --> 00:19:55.899 align:center line:79%
to bring your real thoughts 
and questions to the table.

00:19:56.441 --> 00:19:58.026 align:center line:81%
Alpha is a space where you can say

00:19:58.026 --> 00:20:00.111 align:center line:81%
what you think and how you feel.

00:20:00.153 --> 00:20:01.947 align:center line:81%
This is your space.

00:20:01.947 --> 00:20:04.866 align:center line:81%
So welcome... to the conversation.
